article.headline: Augspurger's big second half lifts Rams
article.linkText: Augspurger's 19 points lift Colorado State past USF
article.story:
FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- Ashley Augspurger scored 13 of her 19
points in the second half as Colorado State (No. 18 ESPN/USA Today; No. 19 Associated Press) beat San
Francisco 76-58 Friday night in the opening round of the preseason
WNIT.

	   Joy Jenkins added 17 points, including three 3-pointers, and had
a steal and a basket in an 11-0 run that put Colorado State (1-0)
ahead 42-29 with 16:08 left.

	   Carey Sauer led San Francisco (0-1) with 17 points. Jennifer
Jones, who along with Toni Russell had 10 points, got the Dons
to 48-38 down with a basket off an offensive rebound with 11:05 left
in the opening game for both teams.

	   San Francisco never managed to get the deficit to less than double
digits. Augspurger hit a 3-pointer and Jenkins converted two free
throws in a 7-0 run that put Colorado State ahead 55-38.

	   Russell's driving layup with 5:05 left cut the lead to 63-50,
but Augspurger put the game out of reach with two layups of her
own.

	   Colorado State led by as many as nine points in the first half
as Jenkins scored 10 points. Merisa Leatherman's three-point play
and a running layup by Russell got San Francisco to 31-27 by
halftime.

	   The Rams play Southern California, which defeated Northern
Arizona 63-55, in the second round Sunday.
